 
<p>
South Dakota has an optional Indian alternative justice system which
aims for 
<a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2022/aug/06/native-elders-oyate-court-south-dakota">healing rather than punishment.</a>
<p>
In the 1970s, US courts and prisons aimed for rehabilitation of
criminals, but that was all discarded in the 
<a href="https://www.commondreams.org/views/2022/01/05/war-drugs-has-failed-when-disease-becomes-crime">1980s under the malign
influence of the "war on drugs".</a>

 